main event: A round object the size of a baseball was reported over Waupon, Wisconsin on May 6, 1956.
interesting points: The object was described as a light at low altitude, moving from south to north before disappearing.
There were 15 witnesses who observed the object with the naked eye.
The sighting occurred at night, with the object being visible for 3-5 minutes.
The object was located approximately 351 miles northeast of Madison, Wisconsin.
The report was submitted to various military and intelligence agencies, including the 755th ACWV SQ at Williams ARY, Wisconsin.
